Subject: InVentry System Refresh - Marfleet Primary School | CRM:03290892
To: Rebecca Gutherless-wilcox <r.gutherless-wilcox@ebor.academy>


Hi Rebecca

Hope you are well.

Thank you for your purchase of a system refresh.

Please review the attached system refresh preparation document, as this
provides important information about refreshing your InVentry hardware.

Our next available date for your refresh is* 09/02/2023**. *I have reserved
this date for you until* close of business today (24/01/2023)*. If you
could confirm suitability as soon as possible, it would be greatly
appreciated. If we haven’t received confirmation by this date, the
reservation will be removed and we will need to arrange a new date.

We do require your IT support technician to be available to assist the
engineer with network ports/network IP addresses, testing the backup,
testing the MIS, installing Anti-Virus and adding the InVentry admin
software to the various computers.

*Your system will be down whilst the upgrade is taking place. You will need
to have alternative methods in place for signing in and out. *

*We recommend using a paper list to record visitors, staff and pupils
signing in/out and our engineer will be able to add this information into
the newly update Inventry software when the refresh is complete.*

Due to having to carry heavy tools and equipment, we kindly ask if our
engineer can park within your onsite car park. If this is not possible,
please could you advise on nearby parking facilities that our engineer can
use.



Your InVentry equipment is going to be shipped directly to your site before
your installation. It will be directed to the address provided on your
order - this will be marked for your attention. The package will be shipped
in a large, reinforced cardboard box, which will be clearly labelled with
‘InVentry’. This box should only be opened by your InVentry engineer,
otherwise it could void the warranty of your InVentry equipment. The
package will need to be signed for and safely retained within your
organisation, ready for our installation engineer. If you would like the
InVentry equipment to be shipped to a different location or to a different
person, please can you let me by return email as soon as possible.



In the meantime, if you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact
me or one of my colleagues within the scheduling team.

Kind regards

Morning Melanie,

When the install team were on site installing the access control to the site, Vital provided them with a fibre link from the studio back to the pupil support building. The access control was fully operational, but before Christmas the ethernet/ fibre link to the studio has been disconnected, meaning you are unable to control, program or receive any data back from the Paxton access control system . Unfortunately, we are reliant on vital to provide the link required.

Since the installation we are still waiting for the CCtv fibre link to be completed by vital, Currently the CCtv camera on the studio cannot be used. I spoke to a vital technician who was onsite nearing the end of the project, he was amendment the link was nothing to do with them, at the time Pat Dalby, my Engineering Director, and MD were onsite who all agreed that vital were providing all the links, and switches. Vital had provided the networking equipment throughout the upgrade project. As we were nearing the end of the project, we have provided the poe switch with is in the studio’s server cabinet, the poe switch has 2 x gigabit fibre optical ports.

If it could be possible to arrange with Vital to reinstate the access control fibre link between the studio and pupil support building. Then complete a new fibre link for the CCtv camera form the studio to the pupil support building.


Regards,

Hi Helen

Thank you for getting back to me.

I can now confirm that everything is in place to complete your InVentry
system refresh on *25/01/2023**.*

Your engineer is called *Alex Pearson* and will arrive at site between
* 11:30 *and *13:30* to complete your refresh.

Please could you make sure that everything is in place ready for the
engineer to complete the site visit. If there are any issues that arise
outside of InVentry’s control, a chargeable return visit maybe required.

Just a reminder that we do require your IT support technician to assist the
engineer with network ports/network IP addresses. This can be remote or
onsite support.

*PLEASE NOTE: Your system will be down whilst the upgrade is taking place.
You will need to have alternative methods in place for signing in and
out. We recommend using a paper list to record Visitor, Staff and Pupil
Sign In's/ Out's and our engineer will be able to add all of this
information into the newly update Inventry software when the refresh is
complete.*

Due to having to carry heavy tools and equipment, we kindly ask if our
engineer can park within your onsite car park. If this is not possible,
please could you advise on nearby parking facilities that our engineer can
use.



Your InVentry equipment is going to be shipped directly to your before your
installation. It will be directed to the address provided on your order -
this will be marked for your attention. The package will be shipped in a
large, reinforced cardboard box, which will be clearly labelled with
‘InVentry’. This box should only be opened by your InVentry engineer,
otherwise it could void the warranty of your InVentry equipment. The
package will need to be signed for and safely retained within your
organisation, ready for our installation engineer. If you would like the
InVentry equipment to be shipped to a different location or to a different
person, please can you let me by return email as soon as possible.

In the meantime, if you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact
me or one of my colleagues within the scheduling team.

Hi Lyn

I have just tried to call you but was unable to get through.

Thank you for your purchase of a system refresh.

Please review the attached system refresh preparation document, as this
provides important information about refreshing your InVentry hardware.

Our next available date for your refresh is* 20/01/2023 for a late
morning/early afternoon appointment**. *I have reserved this date for you
until* 10am tomorrow (13/01/2023)*. If you could confirm suitability as
soon as possible, it would be greatly appreciated. If we haven’t received
confirmation by this date, the reservation will be removed and we will need
to arrange a new date.

We do require your IT support technician to be available to assist the
engineer with network ports/network IP addresses, testing the backup,
testing the MIS, installing Anti-Virus and adding the InVentry admin
software to the various computers.

*Your system will be down whilst the upgrade is taking place. You will need
to have alternative methods in place for signing in and out. *

*We recommend using a paper list to record visitors, staff and pupils
signing in/out and our engineer will be able to add this information into
the newly update Inventry software when the refresh is complete.*

Due to having to carry heavy tools and equipment, we kindly ask if our
engineer can park within your onsite car park. If this is not possible,
please could you advise on nearby parking facilities that our engineer can
use.



Your InVentry equipment is going to be shipped directly to your site before
your installation. It will be directed to the address provided on your
order - this will be marked for your attention. The package will be shipped
in a large, reinforced cardboard box, which will be clearly labelled with
‘InVentry’. This box should only be opened by your InVentry engineer,
otherwise it could void the warranty of your InVentry equipment. The
package will need to be signed for and safely retained within your
organisation, ready for our installation engineer. If you would like the
InVentry equipment to be shipped to a different location or to a different
person, please can you let me by return email as soon as possible.



In the meantime, if you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact
me or one of my colleagues within the scheduling team.

To: Lindsay Wilson <l.wilson@ebor.academy>


Hi Lindsay

Following on from our telephone conversation.

I can now confirm that everything is in place to complete your InVentry
system refresh on *12/01/2023**.*

Your engineer is called *Alex Pearson* and will arrive at site between
* 12:00 *and *14:00* to complete your refresh.

Please could you make sure that everything is in place ready for the
engineer to complete the site visit. If there are any issues that arise
outside of InVentry’s control, a chargeable return visit maybe required.

Just a reminder that we do require your IT support technician to assist the
engineer with network ports/network IP addresses. This can be remote or
onsite support.

*PLEASE NOTE: Your system will be down whilst the upgrade is taking place.
You will need to have alternative methods in place for signing in and
out. We recommend using a paper list to record Visitor, Staff and Pupil
Sign In's/ Out's and our engineer will be able to add all of this
information into the newly update Inventry software when the refresh is
complete.*

Due to having to carry heavy tools and equipment, we kindly ask if our
engineer can park within your onsite car park. If this is not possible,
please could you advise on nearby parking facilities that our engineer can
use.



Your InVentry equipment is going to be shipped directly to your before your
installation. It will be directed to the address provided on your order -
this will be marked for your attention. The package will be shipped in a
large, reinforced cardboard box, which will be clearly labelled with
‘InVentry’. This box should only be opened by your InVentry engineer,
otherwise it could void the warranty of your InVentry equipment. The
package will need to be signed for and safely retained within your
organisation, ready for our installation engineer. If you would like the
InVentry equipment to be shipped to a different location or to a different
person, please can you let me by return email as soon as possible.

In the meantime, if you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact
me or one of my colleagues within the scheduling team.

Kind regards

From: Chloe Ellis <Chloe.Ellis@inventry.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 10 Jan 2023 at 11:20
Subject: InVentry System Refresh - Haxby Road Primary Academy | CRM:03290710
To: Tracey Long <t.long@ebor.academy>


Hi Tracey

I have just tried to call you but unfortunatley I was unable to get
through.

Thank you for your purchase of a system refresh.

Please review the attached system refresh preparation document, as this
provides important information about refreshing your InVentry hardware.

Our next available date for your refresh is* 17/01/2023**. *I have reserved
this date for you until* close of business today (10/01/2023)*. If you
could confirm suitability as soon as possible, it would be greatly
appreciated. If we haven’t received confirmation by this date, the
reservation will be removed and we will need to arrange a new date.

We do require your IT support technician to be available to assist the
engineer with network ports/network IP addresses, testing the backup,
testing the MIS, installing Anti-Virus and adding the InVentry admin
software to the various computers.

*Your system will be down whilst the upgrade is taking place. You will need
to have alternative methods in place for signing in and out. *

*We recommend using a paper list to record visitors, staff and pupils
signing in/out and our engineer will be able to add this information into
the newly update Inventry software when the refresh is complete.*

Due to having to carry heavy tools and equipment, we kindly ask if our
engineer can park within your onsite car park. If this is not possible,
please could you advise on nearby parking facilities that our engineer can
use.



Your InVentry equipment is going to be shipped directly to your site before
your installation. It will be directed to the address provided on your
order - this will be marked for your attention. The package will be shipped
in a large, reinforced cardboard box, which will be clearly labelled with
‘InVentry’. This box should only be opened by your InVentry engineer,
otherwise it could void the warranty of your InVentry equipment. The
package will need to be signed for and safely retained within your
organisation, ready for our installation engineer. If you would like the
InVentry equipment to be shipped to a different location or to a different
person, please can you let me by return email as soon as possible.



In the meantime, if you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact
me or one of my colleagues within the scheduling team.

Kind regards

[required] Title: Re: Period 2 Thursday Walking Talking Mock each week to half term
Description:
Hi All,

Not to throw a spanner in the works but has consideration been given with
regards to the number of students and tables required alongside the fire
safety limitations of the Hall and the preparation and removal time?

If you are putting 200 students into the main Hall, you would by your
calculations need around 34 desks putting out. When you put six people
around each desk there is not going to be enough space to allow for safe
evacuation in case of a fire.

We also have an issue with staffing to complete this task from a site point
of view. Ian is needed at George Pindar on Thursdays and only one member of
the site team is currently able to put these desks out which would be a
difficult undertaking in the hour after the assembly has finished.

I would like to try and resolve this for you though, are the tables
definitely needed?

Thanks

Mark Ward

Support Services Manager

Moor Lane | Eastfield | Scarborough | YO11 3LW

Description:

She has asked us if we can set up some form of Google locations they can work from together, almost as if they were part of the same trust, or a drive that can be shared across both domains.

Currently both schools have each others domain whitelisted so can use folders/docs as such but are pushing for more seamless collaborative working

Subject: RE: Clicker support - CAS-10525
To: Mrs Murray <smurray@dringhouses.co.uk>


Hi Sarah



Thanks for getting in touch again, and for sending over that picture. Happy
New Year!



To confirm, 1-7 are licensed, while 8, 9 and 10 aren’t yet.

If you were using 1-7 and this still appeared, pop-ups may be blocked.
Google has made a change that causes the account log-in window to need to
appear every time Clicker Writer is opened, and that’s classed as a pop-up.

We require the Google login for licensing. Therefore, for licensing to
work, we need pop-ups to be enabled on our apps.

Please send this information over to your IT Support:

The URLs to whitelist in Google Admin are:
https://clickerwriter.apps.cricksoft.com
https://clickerbooks.apps.cricksoft.com
https://clickertalk.apps.cricksoft.com

Within the Google Admin console, the URL whitelist can be found in: Devices
> Chrome > Settings > Users & browsers. From there, where it says “Search
or add a filter”, type “Pop-up”. It should be listed under “Content”.

Kind regards



Tyler Corrigan

Support Analyst



We welcome your feedback
<https://analytics-eu.clickdimensions.com/cricksoftcom-antjv/pages/n9s4kqp8eey25gaisd9d7w.html?PageId=91b8d437fc03ec11b6e60022483f5def>

Hi Julie



Following on from our telephone conversation.



I can now confirm that everything is in place to complete your InVentry
system refresh on *11/01/2023.*



Your engineer is called *Matthew Jarrett* and will arrive at site between
*08:30* and *09:00* to complete your refresh.

Please could you make sure that everything is in place ready for the
engineer to complete the site visit. If there are any issues that arise
outside of InVentry’s control, a chargeable return visit maybe required.

Just a reminder that we do require your IT support technician to assist the
engineer with network ports/network IP addresses. This can be remote or
onsite support.

*PLEASE NOTE: Your system will be down whilst the upgrade is taking place.
You will need to have alternative methods in place for signing in and
out. We recommend using a paper list to record Visitor, Staff and Pupil
Sign In's/ Out's and our engineer will be able to add all of this
information into the newly update Inventry software when the refresh is
complete.*

Due to having to carry heavy tools and equipment, we kindly ask if our
engineer can park within your onsite car park. If this is not possible,
please could you advise on nearby parking facilities that our engineer can
use.



Your InVentry equipment is going to be shipped directly to your before your
installation. It will be directed to the address provided on your order -
this will be marked for your attention. The package will be shipped in a
large, reinforced cardboard box, which will be clearly labelled with
‘InVentry’. This box should only be opened by your InVentry engineer,
otherwise it could void the warranty of your InVentry equipment. The
package will need to be signed for and safely retained within your
organisation, ready for our installation engineer. If you would like the
InVentry equipment to be shipped to a different location or to a different
person, please can you let me by return email as soon as possible.

In the meantime, if you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact
me or one of my colleagues within the scheduling team.

Kind regards

note that at this stage of the process we are simply reviewing whether the
school requires funding or not, and a huge amount of technical detail is
not required. *This section can be left blank.*

rooms/ cabinet locations are set up that may be a problem in upgrading the
network, please note it here.** eg the school has a number of small wall
mounted cabinets that would benefit from being consolidated together.*

Passive network

*If there is anything unusual or complex about the way the buildings are
cabled that might be an issue, please note it here.** eg there are faults
with the cabling that would service some wireless access points which will
need replacing.*

Building Interconnects

*If there is anything unusual or complex about the way buildings at the
site are networked together, please note it here.** eg there is an
outbuilding that currently has classes but does not have a network
connection.*

Immediate Plans

*If there are any significant changes at the site (such as building works)
taking place in the next 12 months, please use this space to let us know.**
eg the school is having a major refurbishment in the infants block at the
start of 2023 and any networking changes would be better timed for the
completion of that work.*

Other

networking at the site in the coming 12 months, please mention it here**.
eg the school is in the process of joining XXXX Academy Trust and they

Hello,

I'm having some trouble using Javafx on the school computers, and having done some searching into the issue, most of the solutions involve using the terminal, which I'm unable to do on the school computers.

I'm not fully able to explain the problem as I'm not sure I understand it, but originally, the fxml file in the target folder was saying that the URI http://javafx.com/fxml wasn't recognised, so I added it to the sources in the settings, to which it said the resource registered by the URI wasn't recognised. I went into the settings again to direct it to the javafx files in my external libraries folder, and now it says that none of the javafx attributes are defined, despite them being imported at the top of the file.

I've tried several of the javafx files in that folder, including two specifically labelled fxml. I've also tried adding the URI to the "Ignored schemas and DTDs" list, but this just caused the error that VBox wasn't defined.

I know you can't help with programming issues, but I think I've exhausted all programming-related solutions, and this must be an issue with the school computers. It was working when we first started development, and I stopped using fxml for a few weeks to test and prepare other parts of the code, and then it stopped working when I tried to use the same code from before.

Would it be possible to check that fxml is set up on the computers properly?

Thanks in advance and merry Christmas,
Jess WG
13NLB

Hi James

We are aiming to complete our Criminology controlled assessment with students in January. This is an 8 hour internal assessment that can be split over multiple sessions - but all require computer access.

We have two classes which equate to 35 students

For this assessment the following protocols are required

For the first 3 hours of tasks, students are not allowed to have internet access
For the remaining 5 hours of tasks students are allowed internet access as they need to design campaign materials using websites.
Students need to be able to save their work electronically but are not permitted to have access to this outside of the controlled assessment (so unable to use student area/teams etc)
If you could let me know how best we can facilitate this that would be great
Thanks

David
